                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.602 Ot 81/258: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-12T12:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1923—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received April 12—11:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>104. French High Commissioner presented yesterday to Angora representative formal
                    note of protest against adoption of the Chester project by Assembly. Am
                    following situation closely and will telegraph details later.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
